The paper deals with the secrecy capacity of a wiretap channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of secure feedback and shared-key generation also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR). The consideration of causal state information and the use of feedback for secure communication also suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). The use of coding schemes and shared-key generation also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the consideration of special cases and the use of feedback for transmitting state information suggest that the paper may belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
